  <thing id="fStrongMin" name="Strong Mind" description="{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Wis 11\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You gain an +3 bonus on saving throws against psionic abilities and  mind attacks. Psionic abilities include spell-like abilities of monsters such as Aboleths, Mind-flayers, and Yuan-Ti (and any other creatures whose special attacks are described as psionic).\n\nMind attacks include the Mind-flayer&apos;s {i}Mind Blast{/i} ability, as well as any similiar supernatural ability that uses sheer mental force to stun or disable an opponent (at the DM&apos;s discretion).\n\n{b}Special{/b}: The benefit of this feat does not extend to spells, spell-like abilities , or magic items that duplicate psionic abilities. This is an exception to the general rule that magic and psionics are equivalent." compset="Feat" summary="+3 Bonus on saving throws versus Psionics." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="EbCamSet" parent="pECS" name="Eberron Campaign Setting"/>
