  <thing id="sArt4004" name="Iron Construct" description="You transform an existing construct into a powerhouse of hardened iron, similar to the effect of the iron body spell. The construct gains damage reduction 15/adamantine. It takes half damage from acid and fire attacks of all kinds. Even if it is not a golem, however, it becomes vulnerable to all special attacks that affect iron golems.\n\nThe construct gains a +4 enhancement bonus to Strength, but takes a &#150;4 penalty to Dexterity as well (to a minimum Dexterity of 1).\n\nThe construct&#146;s weight increases by a factor of five.\n\n{i}Material Component{/i}: A small piece of iron that was once part of an iron golem, a hero&#146;s armor, or a war machine." compset="Spell" summary="Construct gains DR 15/adamantine and takes half damage from acid and fire.">
