  <thing id="fBindEleme" name="Bind Elemental" description="You can craft magic items that use bound elementals for special effects, including weapons, armor, airships, and elemental galleons.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Craft Wondrous Item, caster level 9th.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Crafting an item with a bound elemental is similar to making a wondrous item, except that calling and binding an elemental is an integral part of creating the item. All bound-elemental items have a {i}planar binding{/i} spell as a prerequisite, but simply casting the spell as part of the item creation is not sufficient. You must cast the spell normally, using the item that is to hold the elemental and a Khyber dragonshard as a receptacle. The elemental receives its normal saving throw to resist. While the elemental resides in the receptacle, you must compel it to accept bondage in the item by making an opposed Charisma check, as specified in the {i}lesser planar binding{/i} spell description.\n\nIf you are an artificer, this feat allows you to cast a {i}planar binding{/i} spell by successfully emulating it with a Use Magic Device check (DC 20 + caster level), but only when you attempt to craft a bound-elemental item. In this case, your effective caster level equals your Use Magic Device check result &#150;20 for the purpose of opposing the elemental&#146;s attempts to escape." compset="Feat" summary="Create bound-elemental items">
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="ItemCreate"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Craft Wondrous Item required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fCraftWond] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <prereq message="Caster level 9th required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[if (herofield[tMaxCaster].value >= 9) then
  @valid = 1
elseif (tagcount[Classes.Artificer] >= 1) then
  if (hero.child[cHelpArt].field[cCasterLev].value >= 9) then
    @valid = 1
  endif
endif]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipEbBurnA" name="Burning" description="A Large fire elemental is bound into this armor, which smolders with a reddish glow. The wearer of this armor gains resistance to cold 10. Three times per day, the wearer can command the armor to burst into flames. The flames do not harm the wearer, but any creature hitting the wearer with its body or a handheld weapon takes 2d6 points of fire damage and also catches on fire unless it succeeds on a DC 17 Reflex save. Creatures wielding reach weapons, such as longspears, are not subject to this damage. The flames last for 11 rounds.\n\n{b}Moderate conjuration{/b}; CL 11th; Bind Elemental, {i}planar binding{/i}; Price +90,000 gp." compset="ItemPower" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="iPriceCash" value="90000"/>
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Armor"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipEbStonem" name="Stonemeld" description="A Large earth elemental is bound into this armor, and crystalline structures appear on various areas of its surface. The wearer of this armor gains damage reduction 5/&#151; and can use meld into stone on command three times per day.\n\n{b}Moderate conjuration{/b}; CL 11th; Bind Elemental, {i}planar binding{/i}; Price +80,000 gp." compset="ItemPower" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="iPriceCash" value="80000"/>
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Armor"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipEbUndAct" name="Underwater Action" description="A Large water elemental is bound into this armor, giving it a milky blue-white appearance. The wearer of this armor can breathe water as if under the effect of a water breathing spell, and the armor imposes no armor check penalty on Swim checks. Twice per day, the wearer can command the armor to produce a quench effect.\n\n{b}Moderate conjuration{/b}; CL 11th; Bind Elemental, {i}planar binding{/i}; Price +86,000 gp." compset="ItemPower" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="iPriceCash" value="86000"/>
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Armor"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipEbWhirlw" name="Whirlwind" description="A Large air elemental is bound into this armor, which takes on an almost translucent appearance. When the wearer of this armor speaks a command word, the armor allows him to f ly at a speed of 60 feet (good maneuverability). Once per day the wearer can transform himself (and all his gear) into a whirlwind exactly as though he were a Large air elemental, remaining in that form for up to 4 rounds.\n\n{b}Moderate conjuration{/b}; CL 11th; Bind Elemental, {i}planar binding{/i}; Price +90,000 gp." compset="ItemPower" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="iPriceCash" value="90000"/>
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Armor"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipEbBurnW" name="Burning" description="A burning weapon has a Small fire elemental bound to it, and has all the characteristics of a flaming weapon. In addition, creatures hit by the weapon must succeed on a DC 11 Reflex save or catch on fire. The fame burns for 1d4 rounds. A burning creature can take a move action to put out the flame. The wielder also gains a +2 bonus on his initiative check if he is holding the weapon at the start of combat.\n\n{b}Moderate conjuration{/b}; CL 9th; Bind Elemental, {i}lesser planar binding{/i}; Price +2 bonus." compset="ItemPower" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+2"/>
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipEbEarthb" name="Earthbound" description="An earthbound weapon has a Small earth elemental bound to it, and has a heavy, crystalline appearance. As long as the wielder and his opponent are both touching the ground, the weapon grants its wielder an additional +2 bonus on attack and damage rolls. If the wielder is flying, the weapon&#146;s enhancement bonus from this property does not apply to his attacks (though the +1 enhancement bonus on his attack rolls for using a masterwork weapon still applies).\n\n{b}Moderate conjuration{/b}; CL 9th; Bind Elemental, {i}lesser planar binding{/i}; Price +1 bonus." compset="ItemPower" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+1"/>
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipEbFiness" name="Finesse" description="A finesse weapon has a Small air elemental bound to it, and has a slightly translucent appearance. This property can be applied only to a light weapon, a rapier, a whip, or a spiked chain, and its benefits apply only if the wielder is the size of creature that the weapon was made for. The wielder can use a finesse weapon as if he had the Weapon Finesse feat. In addition, the weapon grants a +2 enhancement bonus to the wielder&#146;s Dexterity score.\n\n{b}Moderate conjuration{/b}; CL 9th; Bind Elemental, {i}lesser planar binding{/i}; Price +3 bonus." compset="ItemPower" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+3"/>
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipEbKeepFa" name="Keeper&apos;s Fang" description="The Keeper is the Sovereign Lord of Death and Decay. He is said to have a vast domain hidden beneath the Demon Wastes, populated by souls that he has snatched away from Dolurrh. A Keeper&#146;s fang weapon has been consecrated to the Lord of Death, and incorporates a Khyber shard into the hilt. If it is used to strike a killing blow, the soul of the victim is trapped in the Keeper&#146;s domain, and the victim cannot be brought back to life using resurrection, raise dead, reincarnate, or similar effects. But all is not lost &#151; stories tell of heroes who have found the lair of the Keeper and brought the souls of their companions back from bondage.\n\nA Keeper&#146;s fang weapon is evil-aligned. The blade or stock of the weapon is engraved with the runes of the Keeper; a successful DC 20 Knowledge (religion) check allows a character to recognize the nature and purpose of the weapon. Most followers of the Sovereign Host consider the mere possession of a Keeper&#146;s fang weapon to be an abominable act; the use of the weapon is a heinous and unforgivable crime.\n\nOnly melee weapons can be dedicated as Keeper&#146;s fang weapons.\n\n{b}Moderate conjuration{/b}; CL 17th; Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}align weapon, soul bind{/i}; Price +4 bonus." compset="ItemPower" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+4"/>
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="Melee"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipEbWaterb" name="Waterborn" description="A waterborn weapon has a Small water elemental bound to it, and takes on a milky blue-white appearance. If the weapon is a slashing or bludgeoning weapon, this property negates the normal penalties for using such a weapon underwater, as if the wielder were under the effect of a {i}freedom of movement{/i} spell. If the weapon is a piercing weapon, this property grants an additional +2 bonus on its wielder&#146;s attack rolls and damage rolls when both the wielder and his opponent are touching water.\n\nWhen the wielder of a waterborn weapon uses it from land to attack a creature in the water, this property negates the cover normally granted to swimming creatures against attacks from land, again as if the wielder were under the effect of {i}freedom of movement{/i}.\n\n{b}Moderate conjuration{/b}; CL 9th; Bind Elemental, {i}lesser planar binding{/i}; Price +1 bonus." compset="ItemPower" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="+1"/>
    <usesource source="EbCamSet"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    </thing>
  </document>
